{
  "schemaVersion": 1,
  "description": "Pre-cardConfigs era saber profiles (Phase 3 → pre-Phase 7). Profiles in this shape stored their preset list as a flat `presetEntries[]` array with a sibling `fontAssignments` map. There were NO `cardConfigs`, NO `activeCardConfigId`, NO `description`, and (in the earliest builds) NO `notes`. Loading any of these profiles must run through `migrateProfile()` which: (a) folds `presetEntries` into a single auto-generated `cardConfigs[0]` named 'Default', (b) sets `activeCardConfigId` to that new card config's id, and (c) default-fills `notes` + `description` to ''. The new card config + entry IDs are generated via `crypto.randomUUID()`, so the test harness mocks that to produce deterministic 'uuid-1', 'uuid-2', ... values. UUID call order in migrateProfile: each entry's id (in presetEntries order) first, THEN the card config's id last. So for N preset entries, entries get uuid-1..uuid-N and the card config gets uuid-(N+1). For empty presetEntries, the card config alone gets uuid-1. If a fixture starts failing, the migration path has drifted — either the migration logic changed or a new required field was added without a default in the migration.",
